# Git and release

## Workflow

- Target `master` via pull request; CI runs build, test (Node 16/18/20), and lint
- Commit messages: clear and descriptive; add `[skip ci]` only when intentionally skipping release/CI

## Release (from CONTRIBUTING.md)

| Trigger | npm tag |
|---------|---------|
| Push to `master` | `beta` (automatic) |
| GitHub Release published | `latest` (manual) |

## Changelog

Update `CHANGELOG.md` for user-visible changes using the existing format:

```
1.0.x / YYYY-MM-DD
==================
- Description of change
```

## Agent checklist for PRs

1. `npm test` and `npm run lint` pass
2. `CHANGELOG.md` updated if behavior or API changed
3. No manual edits under `dist/`
4. No unintended scope creep (formatting, charts, etc.)
